      <item>
        <title>Using JavaScript ES6 import/export modules</title>
        <description>&lt;h3&gt;How to use ES6 modules in your browser&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can include a module in your HTML by adding a script with &lt;mark&gt;&lt;code&gt;type=&quot;module&quot;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/mark&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-markup&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;script type=&quot;module&quot;&amp;gt;
    import {helloWorld} from './hello-world.js';
    helloWorld();
&amp;lt;/script&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-javascript&quot;&gt;const helloWorld = () =&amp;gt; alert ('Hello World!');
export {
